This paper deals with computational models of word similarity and association, which are topics related to natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses regression and predictive modeling tools, which are common in the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with semantic relatedness, which is a topic in cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the development of psychological process models, which could be relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
